Bulgaria, the real estate paradise of the EU
The development of the Bulgarian real estate market is admirable - the attention of all Europe is directed towards that Balkan country just mentioned.
What, where and who buys in the even cheaper EU market, which will quickly become more expensive?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of Re/Max.
The preferred target for real estate purchases in Eastern Europe is undoubtedly some Bulgaria, with its cheap apartments from the ski slopes and the villas from the beaches.
The mountainous regions of Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa are the most preferred, while in the beaches of Albena, the "Golden Coast", the "Sun Coast", the ancient Sozopol and Nesebar, but more and more people are looking for properties also in the surroundings of Kavarna and Balchik.
According to Re/Max analysts in Bulgaria, sooner or later also the central area of the country - such as Veliko Tarnovo, Gabrovo, Elena, Triavna - will arouse the interest of real estate developers and more and more people will buy real estate in the especially cheap area of Rus.
Similarly, the capital Sofia will be attractive, the commercial and office spaces promise a rapid recovery of the investment.
Bulgaria is on the best way to become one of the most attractive golf paradises in Europe, thus being a prominent destination also during the other two seasons, in addition to summer and winter.
Therefore, cautious investors are already making their purchases, for example in the vicinity of Bansko.
According to analysts, those who buy real estate in Bulgaria are also striving to change their lives and way of life.
Most of the customers are English, but they also come from France, Belgium, Spain and increasingly from Romania.
Also present are the Maltese and Cypriot promoters and traditionally there are many Russian customers on the beaches of the Black Sea and in the skiing paradises.
Foreign customers can be classified into three groups - says Georgi Jankov, regional director of Re/Max in Bulgaria.
Those who intend to settle here buy new or renovated properties for a price between 50 and 100 thousand euros or old houses in poor condition between 5 and 15 thousand euros, to renovate them later.
They require good communication and access, in addition to them the proximity of a large city, shops and usually a local doctor is important.
The second category consists of the buyers of villas (Bulgaria in December was included in the top 10 holiday destinations of the Germans).
The third group consists of real estate investors who make their purchases in the hope of benefiting in the medium or long term.
The price of capital real estate is constantly growing, as demand is increasing.
Although Bulgaria has the lowest real estate prices in the European Union, in the last five years these have experienced an annual increase of 21 percent.
The rise in the price of real estate far outweighs wage growth.
Fodor and the six hundred Hungarians
According to the Minister of Environment and Hydrology G<0xC3><0xA1>bor Fodor, the meetings at the expert level will end on Tuesday and on Wednesday after the official inauguration, negotiations at the ministerial level on the international climate regime after 2012 will continue.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries around the world are discussing the Bali Roadmap on post-reduction efforts, as set out in the Kyoto Protocol, in force until 2012.
There are currently lively discussions on the specifics between developing and industrialized countries.
The United States has already indicated that it does not want to negotiate on precise figures at the moment, although it tends to agree that, compared to the situation in 1990, by 2020 emissions of greenhouse gases will decrease by 25 to 40 percent.
Another major theme of the conference is whether or not industrialized countries, in addition to reducing emissions, are willing to offer material and technological assistance to countries in need.
A further agreement was reached on the aid to be offered to developing countries.
The support fund, foreseen in the Kyoto Protocol, will be led by a 16-member board of directors, probably within the UN Global Environment Facility (GEF) - writes the "Piac és Profit".
The Six Percentage of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, Minister of Environment and Hydrology G<0xC3><0xA1>bor Fodor supports the EU’s efforts to maintain its leading role in global climate protection and promote the signing of the new international agreement until 2009.
The minister stated that the EU is committed to reducing by 20 percent its greenhouse gas emissions by 2020, compared to the 1990 level, regardless of whether or not the "post-2012 agreement" will be signed and is willing to commit to reducing by as much as 30 percent if the other major developed regions of the world and the developing countries are also willing to compromise.
G<0xC3><0xA1>bor Fodor noted that the signatory countries of the 1997 Kyoto Protocol pledged to decrease by 5.2 percent, within which the then 15 EU member states pledged to meet an 8 percent decrease.
Hungary’s commitment is to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 6 percent over the period between 1985 and 87, which our country will meet, according to a press release from the Ministry of the Environment.
There is a lot at stake in Bali, since in two years the international agreement on long-term climate policy will have to be signed, because if not, it is certain that its entry into force would be postponed to after 2012. In this case the reduction commitments, assumed in the Kyoto Protocol, would not be immediately followed by a new international system of emission reductions, which was the most recently adopted by the UN.
As a result, the reduction of emissions would be delayed and an increase of more than 2°C in the average temperature of the Earth could not be prevented, a fact that scientists say would have immeasurable and irreversible consequences.
British Army Recruits on YouTube
British army units at a video distributor publish footage of actions filmed in Iraq and Afghanistan to popularize themselves.
First, the British Air Force (RAD) took advantage of YouTube services: special units deployed in Afghanistan since March 2006 are uploading videos of their actions against the Taliban, the BBC reported.
These recordings made with mini cameras mounted on the helmets are controlled in Kandahar’s general body of operations, then sent to London to be uploaded to the Internet.
The political message is inevitable.
There are already 139 recordings from the air force soldiers that have been uploaded in this way to the Internet and its "channel" has already been seen by more than 75,000 people.
The British Ministry of Defence registered in the spring of 2007 under the name "defence headquarters" and publishes videos of both actions perpetrated in Iraq and Afghanistan, while the Commonwealth Office and the multinational forces in Iraq (MNFI) have their own YouTube channel.
Category: Operations in Afghanistan
Originally the air force had uploaded the videos for recruitment purposes, but in the opinion of the Ministry of Defense they also serve to present to the public the true purpose of the presence of the British army abroad.
This kind of propaganda costs practically nothing compared to conventional recruitment television spots - said the BBC defense expert Gordon Mackenzie - on the other hand, inevitably have some political message, since in a specific way they justify the reason for the military actions decided by the government.
The Americans have made a video game.
The army is also concerned about the fact that, in addition to the recklessly edited and censored recordings, there are also amateur videos on the distributor, for example about the death of the soldiers: in the "official" propaganda films, a little hypocritical, the officers speak of maximum losses, without presenting the bloody part of the fighting.
In addition, from the battlefields of Iraq and Afghanistan, numerous videos recorded in real operations have already been uploaded to the Internet, but the British army is only recently taking advantage of this opportunity.
Americans use a slightly different form for recruiting with free downloadable shooting video games, called America's Army, in which in the midst of a more or less real situation the player can put himself directly in place of the soldiers.
