A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while Monday – the day when the final vote on the public health law will be held – will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway transit will be completely stopped and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
