This means, that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the law on public health - did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for the strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the National Assembly’s Monday agenda, it is also possible that the public health law is only voted on at very early hours of the night, or perhaps around midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways will stop working indefinitely, in the morning may stop part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the companies Vol<0xC3><0xA1>n.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half the roads will be closed.
