The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and it has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that next year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America, the holidays are not unified.
Hungarian laws make a difference between a national holiday, a state holiday and a public holiday.
The festive days are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical ephemeris.
We also celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year is a holiday - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and on October 23, a day commemorating the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th we celebrate the foundation of the State, on May 1st the Labor Day, on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day feasts of the Passover of the Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, which is why it is often bridged when there is only one working day before or after the holiday.
In exchange for the extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you can not be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly before or after the party.
This legal norm is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and civil servants.
It is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, due to its function, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24 practically stops life in the country, because according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their vacation during these days.
Next year several of our holidays will coincide with midday or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda will be modified around the Labor Day so that then, for four consecutive days, workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, in exchange for Friday, May 2 being a holiday.
The other change relates to the October 23 holiday: on Saturday, October 18, you will have to work instead of Friday, October 24.
Instead, the coming year during the end of the year party can be rested, since from December 24 will not work anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six Little Deterrents to Bitter Your Colleagues’ Lives
E-mails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that happen to us without realizing it: all of them are part of our daily folklore at work.
You have to decide whether to adapt to small annoyances or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Advice.
“I’m sorry, I forgot to tell you that the marketing department was looking for you,” one of your colleagues said.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
At best, you feel it and try to fix the issue, you may call the marketing department to tell them that you forgot to deliver the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, the issue is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding to sloppy explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can bitter your colleagues’ lives and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There is nothing more annoying than when you want to grab a document, an office tool, or your phone and you don’t find them.
Remember yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but by this morning it disappeared?
Do you find your lost pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly be angry with you for stealing their things.
Do not pick up envelopes or post-it from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out of time.
Are you complaining about your colleagues’ private lives?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Don’t pass on to everyone the information (suggestions) you have about your colleagues’ private lives!
Don’t abuse your colleague’s confidence when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, even if others also know things about him.
Are you on sick leave unnecessarily?
When you call the office and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or well, you feel that that day you prefer to rest; think about what others should do your work, your unwashable tasks, your work in term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you already know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you should stay at home, contact them, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to face your absence the next day.
Hoarseness, laughter, phone calls
Are you caught up in your work, but are you getting rid of your colleagues’ squabbles?
Have you inadvertently heard a phone conversation that would have been better not to hear it?
Don’t annoy your colleagues with your bragging, singing, loud conversations (less when you do them over their heads), kicking them, blaspheming them constantly, expressing your discontent out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if they are not deepening at this time in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don’t blame others if you haven’t finished something in time, forgot to send an important letter or message!
Don’t allude to the chaos eventually reigning in the office, nor to the noise your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can fix your missing!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and slippers: very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Do not wear a comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Don’t be uneasy, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday clothes, elegant and beautiful when your occupation demands it!
