The Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which came into force November 1
In parallel with its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of both coming into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to ensure investor protection and regulate in detail the activities of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
MIFID, which amends the Securities Markets Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various supervisors in the European Union.
The new regulation will allow the provision of financial advisory services to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and will create a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory societies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current exchange managers.
The Law also requires investment services companies to disclose in the market information about the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms and requires them to keep a record of all operations they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economic Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it highlights that securitized debts are considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated by what has happened with the debt of high-risk US mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can perform 30 years after the adoption in 1977 of the royal decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of others, will not require CNMV authorization and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment firms at the same time.
