What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, is a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of the car, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment materializes in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being held liable for the obligation to pay damages in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for this reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics reflect that they have a lower injury rate due to their prudence.
In addition, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and with it the probability of having some kind of failure.
Increasing the frequency increases the chances.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will explain here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when it comes to hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as limited driving experience and the age of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is full-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a whole risk with deductible, so that they get insurance coverage at all risk but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would involve the customer paying a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the client contributes will be pre-set based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," Luis Noguera, chief in charge in Spain of First Europa, an online insurance broker, said in a statement.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, and may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fee.
The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses," clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, as the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended is to hire a whole risk with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when using an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, once past the 'fear of the newcomer'.
However, if the client is married but still has no children it is preferable to negotiate full-risk insurance, as long as their financial situation allows it, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest injury rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one at full risk with deductible (can be this of 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third party extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They conduct a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchise," said Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is advisable to have an all-risk insurance with deductible (this being 150 euros), or one to third party extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
